HEADWORD: Adversaria
<hw>Ad`ver*sa"ri*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>adversaria</ets> (sc. <ets>scripta</ets>), neut. pl. of
<ets>adversarius</ets>.]</ety> <def>A miscellaneous collection of notes,
remarks, or selections; a commonplace book; also, commentaries or
notes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>These parchments are supposed to have been St. Paul's
<qex>adversaria</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Bp. Bull.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adversarious</ent>⟦br⟧
